publisher.intro: Valve Corporation[a] is an American video game developer, publisher, and digital distribution company headquartered in Bellevue, Washington.
publisher.descriptin: Valve was founded in 1996 by former Microsoft employees Gabe Newell and Mike Harrington. Their debut game, the first-person shooter (FPS) Half-Life (1998), was a critical and commercial success; with its realism, scripted sequences and seamless narrative, it had a lasting influence on the FPS genre.

developer.intro: Team Ninja (Japanese: チームニンジャ) is a Japanese video game developer, and a division of Koei Tecmo, founded in 1995 as a part of Tecmo. It is founded and formerly led by Tomonobu Itagaki, later by Yosuke Hayashi, and is best known for the Ninja Gaiden action-adventure game series and the Dead or Alive fighting game series.
developer.descriptin: In 1999, Team Ninja started work on a new Ninja Gaiden project, originally intended for arcades, later for the Dreamcast. Due to Sega exiting the console businesss, development was moved to the PlayStation 2. However, due to the Itagaki being impressed with the technology capabilities of the new Xbox from Microsoft, development was moved to the plattform. Ninja Gaiden would release in 2004 to rave critical acclaim.

developer.descriptin: In 1999, Team Ninja started work on a new Ninja Gaiden project, originally intended for arcades, later for the Dreamcast. Due to Sega exiting the console businesss, development was moved to the PlayStation 2. However, due to the Itagaki being impressed with the technology capabilities of the new Xbox from Microsoft, development was moved to the plattform. Ninja Gaiden would release in 2004 to rave critical acclaim.

publisher.descriptin: Valve was founded in 1996 by former Microsoft employees Gabe Newell and Mike Harrington. Their debut game, the first-person shooter (FPS) Half-Life (1998), was a critical and commercial success; with its realism, scripted sequences and seamless narrative, it had a lasting influence on the FPS genre.

developer.intro: Team Ninja (Japanese: チームニンジャ) is a Japanese video game developer, and a division of Koei Tecmo, founded in 1995 as a part of Tecmo. It is founded and formerly led by Tomonobu Itagaki, later by Yosuke Hayashi, and is best known for the Ninja Gaiden action-adventure game series and the Dead or Alive fighting game series.
developer.descriptin: In 1999, Team Ninja started work on a new Ninja Gaiden project, originally intended for arcades, later for the Dreamcast. Due to Sega exiting the console businesss, development was moved to the PlayStation 2. However, due to the Itagaki being impressed with the technology capabilities of the new Xbox from Microsoft, development was moved to the plattform. Ninja Gaiden would release in 2004 to rave critical acclaim.

Their debut game, the first-person shooter (FPS) Half-Life (1998), was a critical and commercial success; with its realism, scripted sequences and seamless narrative, it had a lasting influence on the FPS genre.

developer.intro: Team Ninja (Japanese: チームニンジャ) is a Japanese video game developer, and a division of Koei Tecmo, founded in 1995 as a part of Tecmo. It is founded and formerly led by Tomonobu Itagaki, later by Yosuke Hayashi, and is best known for the Ninja Gaiden action-adventure game series and the Dead or Alive fighting game series.
developer.descriptin: In 1999, Team Ninja started work on a new Ninja Gaiden project, originally intended for arcades, later for the Dreamcast. Due to Sega exiting the console businesss, development was moved to the PlayStation 2. However, due to the Itagaki being impressed with the technology capabilities of the new Xbox from Microsoft, development was moved to the plattform. Ninja Gaiden would release in 2004 to rave critical acclaim.

publisher.intro: Valve Corporation[a] is an American video game developer, publisher, and digital distribution company headquartered in Bellevue, Washington.
publisher.descriptin: Valve was founded in 1996 by former Microsoft employees Gabe Newell and Mike Harrington. Their debut game, the first-person shooter (FPS) Half-Life (1998), was a critical and commercial success; with its realism, scripted sequences and seamless narrative, it had a lasting influence on the FPS genre.

developer.intro: Team Ninja (Japanese: チームニンジャ) is a Japanese video game developer, and a division of Koei Tecmo, founded in 1995 as a part of Tecmo. It is founded and formerly led by Tomonobu Itagaki, later by Yosuke Hayashi, and is best known for the Ninja Gaiden action-adventure game series and the Dead or Alive fighting game series.
developer.descriptin: In 1999, Team Ninja started work on a new Ninja Gaiden project, originally intended for arcades, later for the Dreamcast. Due to Sega exiting the console businesss, development was moved to the PlayStation 2. However, due to the Itagaki being impressed with the technology capabilities of the new Xbox from Microsoft, development was moved to the plattform. Ninja Gaiden would release in 2004 to rave critical acclaim.

developer.descriptin: In 1999, Team Ninja started work on a new Ninja Gaiden project, originally intended for arcades, later for the Dreamcast. Due to Sega exiting the console businesss, development was moved to the PlayStation 2. However, due to the Itagaki being impressed with the technology capabilities of the new Xbox from Microsoft, development was moved to the plattform. Ninja Gaiden would release in 2004 to rave critical acclaim.

Their debut game, the first-person shooter (FPS) Half-Life (1998), was a critical and commercial success; with its realism, scripted sequences and seamless narrative, it had a lasting influence on the FPS genre.

developer.intro: Team Ninja (Japanese: チームニンジャ) is a Japanese video game developer, and a division of Koei Tecmo, founded in 1995 as a part of Tecmo. It is founded and formerly led by Tomonobu Itagaki, later by Yosuke Hayashi, and is best known for the Ninja Gaiden action-adventure game series and the Dead or Alive fighting game series.
developer.descriptin: In 1999, Team Ninja started work on a new Ninja Gaiden project, originally intended for arcades, later for the Dreamcast. Due to Sega exiting the console businesss, development was moved to the PlayStation 2. However, due to the Itagaki being impressed with the technology capabilities of the new Xbox from Microsoft, development was moved to the plattform. Ninja Gaiden would release in 2004 to rave critical acclaim.

developer.descriptin: In 1999, Team Ninja started work on a new Ninja Gaiden project, originally intended for arcades, later for the Dreamcast. Due to Sega exiting the console businesss, development was moved to the PlayStation 2. However, due to the Itagaki being impressed with the technology capabilities of the new Xbox from Microsoft, development was moved to the plattform. Ninja Gaiden would release in 2004 to rave critical acclaim.

Their debut game, the first-person shooter (FPS) Half-Life (1998), was a critical and commercial success; with its realism, scripted sequences and seamless narrative, it had a lasting influence on the FPS genre.

developer.intro: Team Ninja (Japanese: チームニンジャ) is a Japanese video game developer, and a division of Koei Tecmo, founded in 1995 as a part of Tecmo. It is founded and formerly led by Tomonobu Itagaki, later by Yosuke Hayashi, and is best known for the Ninja Gaiden action-adventure game series and the Dead or Alive fighting game series.
developer.descriptin: In 1999, Team Ninja started work on a new Ninja Gaiden project, originally intended for arcades, later for the Dreamcast. Due to Sega exiting the console businesss, development was moved to the PlayStation 2. However, due to the Itagaki being impressed with the technology capabilities of the new Xbox from Microsoft, development was moved to the plattform. Ninja Gaiden would release in 2004 to rave critical acclaim.

Their debut game, the first-person shooter (FPS) Half-Life (1998), was a critical and commercial success; with its realism, scripted sequences and seamless narrative, it had a lasting influence on the FPS genre.

developer.intro: Team Ninja (Japanese: チームニンジャ) is a Japanese video game developer, and a division of Koei Tecmo, founded in 1995 as a part of Tecmo. It is founded and formerly led by Tomonobu Itagaki, later by Yosuke Hayashi, and is best known for the Ninja Gaiden action-adventure game series and the Dead or Alive fighting game series.
developer.descriptin: In 1999, Team Ninja started work on a new Ninja Gaiden project, originally intended for arcades, later for the Dreamcast. Due to Sega exiting the console businesss, development was moved to the PlayStation 2. However, due to the Itagaki being impressed with the technology capabilities of the new Xbox from Microsoft, development was moved to the plattform. Ninja Gaiden would release in 2004 to rave critical acclaim.

developer.descriptin: In 1999, Team Ninja started work on a new Ninja Gaiden project, originally intended for arcades, later for the Dreamcast. Due to Sega exiting the console businesss, development was moved to the PlayStation 2. However, due to the Itagaki being impressed with the technology capabilities of the new Xbox from Microsoft, development was moved to the plattform. Ninja Gaiden would release in 2004 to rave critical acclaim.

Their debut game, the first-person shooter (FPS) Half-Life (1998), was a critical and commercial success; with its realism, scripted sequences and seamless narrative, it had a lasting influence on the FPS genre.

developer.intro: Team Ninja (Japanese: チームニンジャ) is a Japanese video game developer, and a division of Koei Tecmo, founded in 1995 as a part of Tecmo. It is founded and formerly led by Tomonobu Itagaki, later by Yosuke Hayashi, and is best known for the Ninja Gaiden action-adventure game series and the Dead or Alive fighting game series.
developer.descriptin: In 1999, Team Ninja started work on a new Ninja Gaiden project, originally intended for arcades, later for the Dreamcast. Due to Sega exiting the console businesss, development was moved to the PlayStation 2. However, due to the Itagaki being impressed with the technology capabilities of the new Xbox from Microsoft, development was moved to the plattform. Ninja Gaiden would release in 2004 to rave critical acclaim.

developer.descriptin: In 1999, Team Ninja started work on a new Ninja Gaiden project, originally intended for arcades, later for the Dreamcast. Due to Sega exiting the console businesss, development was moved to the PlayStation 2. However, due to the Itagaki being impressed with the technology capabilities of the new Xbox from Microsoft, development was moved to the plattform. Ninja Gaiden would release in 2004 to rave critical acclaim.

publisher.descriptin: Valve was founded in 1996 by former Microsoft employees Gabe Newell and Mike Harrington. Their debut game, the first-person shooter (FPS) Half-Life (1998), was a critical and commercial success; with its realism, scripted sequences and seamless narrative, it had a lasting influence on the FPS genre.

developer.intro: Team Ninja (Japanese: チームニンジャ) is a Japanese video game developer, and a division of Koei Tecmo, founded in 1995 as a part of Tecmo. It is founded and formerly led by Tomonobu Itagaki, later by Yosuke Hayashi, and is best known for the Ninja Gaiden action-adventure game series and the Dead or Alive fighting game series.
developer.descriptin: In 1999, Team Ninja started work on a new Ninja Gaiden project, originally intended for arcades, later for the Dreamcast. Due to Sega exiting the console businesss, development was moved to the PlayStation 2. However, due to the Itagaki being impressed with the technology capabilities of the new Xbox from Microsoft, development was moved to the plattform. Ninja Gaiden would release in 2004 to rave critical acclaim.

Their debut game, the first-person shooter (FPS) Half-Life (1998), was a critical and commercial success; with its realism, scripted sequences and seamless narrative, it had a lasting influence on the FPS genre.

developer.intro: Team Ninja (Japanese: チームニンジャ) is a Japanese video game developer, and a division of Koei Tecmo, founded in 1995 as a part of Tecmo. It is founded and formerly led by Tomonobu Itagaki, later by Yosuke Hayashi, and is best known for the Ninja Gaiden action-adventure game series and the Dead or Alive fighting game series.
developer.descriptin: In 1999, Team Ninja started work on a new Ninja Gaiden project, originally intended for arcades, later for the Dreamcast. Due to Sega exiting the console businesss, development was moved to the PlayStation 2. However, due to the Itagaki being impressed with the technology capabilities of the new Xbox from Microsoft, development was moved to the plattform. Ninja Gaiden would release in 2004 to rave critical acclaim.

Their debut game, the first-person shooter (FPS) Half-Life (1998), was a critical and commercial success; with its realism, scripted sequences and seamless narrative, it had a lasting influence on the FPS genre.

developer.intro: Team Ninja (Japanese: チームニンジャ) is a Japanese video game developer, and a division of Koei Tecmo, founded in 1995 as a part of Tecmo. It is founded and formerly led by Tomonobu Itagaki, later by Yosuke Hayashi, and is best known for the Ninja Gaiden action-adventure game series and the Dead or Alive fighting game series.
developer.descriptin: In 1999, Team Ninja started work on a new Ninja Gaiden project, originally intended for arcades, later for the Dreamcast. Due to Sega exiting the console businesss, development was moved to the PlayStation 2. However, due to the Itagaki being impressed with the technology capabilities of the new Xbox from Microsoft, development was moved to the plattform. Ninja Gaiden would release in 2004 to rave critical acclaim.

developer.descriptin: In 1999, Team Ninja started work on a new Ninja Gaiden project, originally intended for arcades, later for the Dreamcast. Due to Sega exiting the console businesss, development was moved to the PlayStation 2. However, due to the Itagaki being impressed with the technology capabilities of the new Xbox from Microsoft, development was moved to the plattform. Ninja Gaiden would release in 2004 to rave critical acclaim.

publisher.intro: Valve Corporation[a] is an American video game developer, publisher, and digital distribution company headquartered in Bellevue, Washington.
publisher.descriptin: Valve was founded in 1996 by former Microsoft employees Gabe Newell and Mike Harrington. Their debut game, the first-person shooter (FPS) Half-Life (1998), was a critical and commercial success; with its realism, scripted sequences and seamless narrative, it had a lasting influence on the FPS genre.

developer.intro: Team Ninja (Japanese: チームニンジャ) is a Japanese video game developer, and a division of Koei Tecmo, founded in 1995 as a part of Tecmo. It is founded and formerly led by Tomonobu Itagaki, later by Yosuke Hayashi, and is best known for the Ninja Gaiden action-adventure game series and the Dead or Alive fighting game series.
developer.descriptin: In 1999, Team Ninja started work on a new Ninja Gaiden project, originally intended for arcades, later for the Dreamcast. Due to Sega exiting the console businesss, development was moved to the PlayStation 2. However, due to the Itagaki being impressed with the technology capabilities of the new Xbox from Microsoft, development was moved to the plattform. Ninja Gaiden would release in 2004 to rave critical acclaim.

developer.descriptin: In 1999, Team Ninja started work on a new Ninja Gaiden project, originally intended for arcades, later for the Dreamcast. Due to Sega exiting the console businesss, development was moved to the PlayStation 2. However, due to the Itagaki being impressed with the technology capabilities of the new Xbox from Microsoft, development was moved to the plattform. Ninja Gaiden would release in 2004 to rave critical acclaim.

Their debut game, the first-person shooter (FPS) Half-Life (1998), was a critical and commercial success; with its realism, scripted sequences and seamless narrative, it had a lasting influence on the FPS genre.

developer.intro: Team Ninja (Japanese: チームニンジャ) is a Japanese video game developer, and a division of Koei Tecmo, founded in 1995 as a part of Tecmo. It is founded and formerly led by Tomonobu Itagaki, later by Yosuke Hayashi, and is best known for the Ninja Gaiden action-adventure game series and the Dead or Alive fighting game series.
developer.descriptin: In 1999, Team Ninja started work on a new Ninja Gaiden project, originally intended for arcades, later for the Dreamcast. Due to Sega exiting the console businesss, development was moved to the PlayStation 2. However, due to the Itagaki being impressed with the technology capabilities of the new Xbox from Microsoft, development was moved to the plattform. Ninja Gaiden would release in 2004 to rave critical acclaim.

publisher.intro: Valve Corporation[a] is an American video game developer, publisher, and digital distribution company headquartered in Bellevue, Washington.
publisher.descriptin: Valve was founded in 1996 by former Microsoft employees Gabe Newell and Mike Harrington. Their debut game, the first-person shooter (FPS) Half-Life (1998), was a critical and commercial success; with its realism, scripted sequences and seamless narrative, it had a lasting influence on the FPS genre.

developer.intro: Team Ninja (Japanese: チームニンジャ) is a Japanese video game developer, and a division of Koei Tecmo, founded in 1995 as a part of Tecmo. It is founded and formerly led by Tomonobu Itagaki, later by Yosuke Hayashi, and is best known for the Ninja Gaiden action-adventure game series and the Dead or Alive fighting game series.
developer.descriptin: In 1999, Team Ninja started work on a new Ninja Gaiden project, originally intended for arcades, later for the Dreamcast. Due to Sega exiting the console businesss, development was moved to the PlayStation 2. However, due to the Itagaki being impressed with the technology capabilities of the new Xbox from Microsoft, development was moved to the plattform. Ninja Gaiden would release in 2004 to rave critical acclaim.

developer.descriptin: In 1999, Team Ninja started work on a new Ninja Gaiden project, originally intended for arcades, later for the Dreamcast. Due to Sega exiting the console businesss, development was moved to the PlayStation 2. However, due to the Itagaki being impressed with the technology capabilities of the new Xbox from Microsoft, development was moved to the plattform. Ninja Gaiden would release in 2004 to rave critical acclaim.

publisher.intro: Valve Corporation[a] is an American video game developer, publisher, and digital distribution company headquartered in Bellevue, Washington.
publisher.descriptin: Valve was founded in 1996 by former Microsoft employees Gabe Newell and Mike Harrington. Their debut game, the first-person shooter (FPS) Half-Life (1998), was a critical and commercial success; with its realism, scripted sequences and seamless narrative, it had a lasting influence on the FPS genre.
